1
00:00:46,559 --> 00:00:47,760
Help! Help me!

2
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:50,360
Finally awake, huh? Saturn

3
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:50,960
I'm not him...

4
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:51,639
I'm not...

5
00:00:51,639 --> 00:00:52,840
Shut up!

6
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:55,559
Save your excuses.

7
00:00:58,559 --> 00:01:01,239
Please, sit down first,
Grandmother.

8
00:01:03,880 --> 00:01:05,920
Here are your Inhalant

9
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:09,519
Please don't worry too much.

10
00:01:09,519 --> 00:01:10,320
I'm sure

11
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,840
it's nothing serious.

12
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:14,119
Exactly. It has to be.

13
00:01:14,119 --> 00:01:16,679
Unless something
terrible happened...

14
00:01:16,679 --> 00:01:19,280
...my grandson would
never miss this event.

15
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:19,960
Auntie.

16
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:22,199
The guests have all left.

17
00:01:22,960 --> 00:01:26,119
Have you found him yet?

18
00:01:26,119 --> 00:01:27,320
Auntie, please.

19
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:29,639
That precious grandson of yours...

20
00:01:29,639 --> 00:01:32,559
...is probably out partying
somewhere by now.

21
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:35,440
Even though I explicitly told him...

22
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:37,000
...that today is crucial.

23
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,880
It’s your big birthday celebration.

24
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:40,320
The place was packed with guests.

25
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:41,239
And on top of that...

26
00:01:41,239 --> 00:01:42,800
...we were supposed to
announce the new executive...

27
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:45,280
...who will inherit your legacy

28
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:47,039
Khun Ying Dao Kang Fah.

29
00:01:48,159 --> 00:01:48,679
I know.

30
00:01:48,679 --> 00:01:51,880
I’m just afraid something
bad happened to him.

31
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:54,960
Bad? Please.

32
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:56,519
He's just good for nothing.

33
00:01:56,519 --> 00:01:57,360
That kid...

34
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,719
...has zero respect for his elders.

35
00:01:58,719 --> 00:02:01,079
Look at this.
He just decided not to show up?"

36
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:02,280
Unacceptable.

37
00:02:02,280 --> 00:02:03,480
If I were you...

38
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:04,440
...I’d cut him out of the will.

39
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:05,480
I wouldn't leave him a single cent.

40
00:02:05,599 --> 00:02:06,519
Enough!

41
00:02:06,519 --> 00:02:07,840
Stop speaking ill of

42
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,639
my grandson this instant.

43
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,559
It’s because of you!

44
00:02:16,559 --> 00:02:18,119
My brother had to kill himself!

45
00:02:18,119 --> 00:02:19,039
You killed him!

46
00:02:19,239 --> 00:02:19,840
Don't!

47
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,199
You deserve to die too!

48
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,920
Stop! Pakin, don’t!

49
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,360
Pakin!

50
00:02:24,639 --> 00:02:26,199
Are you really going to kill him?

51
00:02:26,199 --> 00:02:27,320
Calm down!

52
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:32,800
Nai’s life must be paid for
with his!

53
00:02:43,679 --> 00:02:45,320
Hey! Hey!

54
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:45,960
Pakinai

55
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:46,599
Pakinai

56
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,239
Stay with me

57
00:02:49,239 --> 00:02:52,480
I won't let you die.
Do you hear me?

58
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:55,000
Think carefully about
what you're doing!

59
00:03:09,639 --> 00:03:12,519
Just accept your fate, Saturn.

60
00:03:14,159 --> 00:03:16,079
Do you know something?

61
00:03:16,079 --> 00:03:17,519
Someone like Phakin....

62
00:03:17,519 --> 00:03:19,480
if anyone hurts him,

63
00:03:19,679 --> 00:03:21,840
he always pays them back.

64
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,840
And this time,

65
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:27,239
you hurt him deep.

66
00:03:27,239 --> 00:03:29,400
He’s never letting you go.

67
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:31,440
You’re done for.

68
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:35,079
There is no escaping this hell.

69
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,159
Mavin

70
00:03:42,159 --> 00:03:43,280
I suspect

71
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,679
there’s something fishy going on.

72
00:03:44,679 --> 00:03:47,880
Otherwise, my grandson
wouldn't just vanish into thin air.

73
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,280
Please don't worry, Madame.

74
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,719
I will do whatever it takes.

75
00:03:50,719 --> 00:03:52,159
I will turn the world upside down

76
00:03:52,159 --> 00:03:54,159
to find your grandson.

77
00:03:54,159 --> 00:03:54,840
Don't be nosy

78
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:59,360
Mavin You're just a
personal secretary.

79
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:01,760
Don't overstep your boundaries.

80
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:03,400
Useless busybody.

81
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,360
Ms. Khaeng Khae

82
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:08,679
Khae! Why are you speaking
to Mavin like that?

83
00:04:09,039 --> 00:04:10,880
Well...I'm just afraid that

84
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,440
having too many people involved

85
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:13,719
will only make a mess.

86
00:04:13,719 --> 00:04:15,719
Besides, I’ve already
sent my people

87
00:04:15,719 --> 00:04:17,440
to handle it.

88
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:19,679
Mavin, proceed with my orders.

89
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,639
Yes, Ma'am.

90
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,679
Auntie, you don't trust that I can

91
00:04:25,679 --> 00:04:27,559
handle this, do you?

92
00:04:29,039 --> 00:04:30,719
What’s wrong with helping

93
00:04:30,719 --> 00:04:32,000
each other find my grandson?

94
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,920
but

95
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,039
Enough.

96
00:04:34,239 --> 00:04:35,800
I know you’ve held a
grudge against Mavin

97
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,320
ever since I had him audit

98
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:39,360
the hotel’s accounts.

99
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:41,159
But what's done is done.

100
00:04:41,159 --> 00:04:42,920
We still have to work together.

101
00:04:43,559 --> 00:04:43,920
Yes, Auntie.

102
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:46,800
Frankly speaking, Auntie...

103
00:04:47,599 --> 00:04:49,559
...ever since Tawan and
Jannipa passed away...

104
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:53,519
I'm the only one who has
done everything for this hotel.

105
00:04:54,719 --> 00:04:57,440
And now, you're acting like
you don't trust me.

106
00:04:58,199 --> 00:04:59,480
It’s not about trust.

107
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:01,360
But since I’ve decided

108
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:03,400
to hand everything over
to my grandson

109
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,440
I want to ensure
everything is flawless.

110
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,880
Absolutely no mistakes.

111
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,639
Yes, Auntie.

112
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,199
Well? What's the deal?

113
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,159
You hungry? Huh?

114
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,000
Auntie...

115
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:31,760
Who are you calling 'Auntie'?

116
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:33,760
I ain't your mother's sister.

117
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,639
Don't you 'Auntie' me.

118
00:05:35,639 --> 00:05:37,960
The name is Thongtae...
oops, no, not Thong...

119
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:39,360
the name is Tammy.

120
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,800
Call me Miss Tammy.

121
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:44,159
Got it? Miss Tammy.

122
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:47,840
Miss Tammy

123
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:48,719
Mmm. What?

124
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:51,360
I'm not Saturn.

125
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:54,639
Yeah,

126
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,760
right. I'll try to believe you.

127
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:59,119
You have to believe me

128
00:05:59,119 --> 00:06:01,119
I'm really not him.

129
00:06:01,119 --> 00:06:03,840
Sure, I'll try.

130
00:06:04,760 --> 00:06:06,639
You're a clever one, aren't you?

131
00:06:06,639 --> 00:06:07,920
Making up stories

132
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:11,239
just to save your own neck.

133
00:06:11,239 --> 00:06:12,920
I'm not stupid, you know.

134
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:16,039
My name is Venus.

135
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:18,480
Saturn is my twin brother.

136
00:06:20,079 --> 00:06:22,079
We might have the same face...

137
00:06:22,079 --> 00:06:22,960
but our personalities

138
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:24,519
are polar opposites

139
00:06:26,079 --> 00:06:28,199
Like oil and water.

140
00:06:28,239 --> 00:06:31,280
And which one are you?
Water or oil?

141
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:33,360
I must be the water

142
00:06:35,599 --> 00:06:38,800
I hope you really are the water.

143
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:43,360
I'm afraid you might be oil..

144
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,000
Corpse Oil.

145
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,199
Look at Phakinai.

146
00:06:49,199 --> 00:06:52,119
He's so under your spell
he'd die for you.

147
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:57,199
Me?

148
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:59,159
I prefer being alone.

149
00:06:59,159 --> 00:07:01,119
Just doing what I love

150
00:07:01,119 --> 00:07:02,679
makes me happy enough.

151
00:07:02,679 --> 00:07:03,159
Hm

152
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:05,559
Those flowers are beautiful,
P'Dao.

153
00:07:05,559 --> 00:07:08,639
Who's the lucky person
receiving them?

154
00:07:08,639 --> 00:07:10,039
No one, Lookkai.

155
00:07:11,119 --> 00:07:13,079
I just love flowers.

156
00:07:13,079 --> 00:07:14,480
Sometimes

157
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:16,760
I wish flowers were everywhere.

158
00:07:18,519 --> 00:07:23,280
Since no one gives us flowers

159
00:07:24,159 --> 00:07:27,000
there's nothing wrong with
giving them to ourselves, right?

160
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:28,000
That's true.

161
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:32,280
We can create our own happiness.

162
00:07:33,239 --> 00:07:34,880
We don't have to wait for
someone else to give it to us.

163
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:35,840
Right?

164
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:38,079
You're absolutely right

165
00:07:42,639 --> 00:07:44,480
As for Saturn

166
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,280
he's more like oil.

167
00:07:46,280 --> 00:07:48,599
Ready to catch fire
at any moment.

168
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:50,480
Burning with passion,

169
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:53,679
like a star that shines
everywhere he goes.

170
00:07:53,679 --> 00:07:54,880
Ever since we were kids

171
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:55,559
Saturn has always

172
00:07:55,559 --> 00:07:57,599
been full of confidence.

173
00:07:58,320 --> 00:07:59,599
Once he hit his teenage years

174
00:08:00,119 --> 00:08:01,880
he was never short of lovers.

175
00:08:03,679 --> 00:08:05,519
But what Saturn wants

176
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,039
is more than just love.

177
00:08:07,039 --> 00:08:09,199
He desires someone
who loves him

178
00:08:09,199 --> 00:08:11,039
and is ready to worship him.

179
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:13,000
Saturn

180
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,800
I love you.

181
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:16,319
With all my life.

182
00:08:17,479 --> 00:08:18,319
You're all I have.

183
00:08:21,479 --> 00:08:23,640
Then prove it to me.

184
00:08:27,479 --> 00:08:30,279
Someday, I'll make you realize

185
00:08:31,159 --> 00:08:32,680
that my entire life

186
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:34,520
is always yours to take

187
00:08:35,399 --> 00:08:36,159
But for now

188
00:08:37,279 --> 00:08:39,560
Can I be the rings that orbit Saturn

189
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:42,039
forever?

190
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:43,199
Show me, then.

191
00:09:16,039 --> 00:09:18,239
Stop, stop, stop!
That's enough, no more stories.

192
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:24,000
Hey, wait a minute.
This story you just told

193
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,239
Was that really
your brother, Saturn

194
00:09:26,239 --> 00:09:27,840
or was it actually you, huh?

195
00:09:29,119 --> 00:09:30,119
Of course it was Saturn.

196
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:32,319
Ooh, but you seemed
way too into it.

197
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:35,000
Everything I just told you

198
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,239
was just to prove that

199
00:09:36,239 --> 00:09:39,039
I am Venus , not Saturn.

200
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,359
And I have absolutely
nothing to do

201
00:09:41,359 --> 00:09:41,920
with Phakinai,

202
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:43,920
Phakin's younger brother.

203
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:44,680
Liar!

204
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:45,239
Khun Pakin!

205
00:09:45,239 --> 00:09:46,319
Pakin, don't!

206
00:09:46,319 --> 00:09:47,239
Don't! Don't! Don't!

207
00:09:54,239 --> 00:09:55,800
Untie the ropes.

208
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,520
I said, untie the ropes!

209
00:10:02,159 --> 00:10:03,880
Hurry up!

210
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,439
Stop dragging your feet!

211
00:10:12,359 --> 00:10:13,680
Take it easy.

212
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:17,840
Come here.
